# Introduction

"http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/Perl_compatible_regular_expressions&quot;

In this tip. I introduced a plugin to help you use Perl style regular expression in Vim.
But the maintainer is disappear. And the default package is not easy to install.
So I start to maintain it.

Repo: http://github.com/othree/eregex.vim


# Quick Start

Add the following code to .vimrc file.

nnoremap / :M/
nnoremap ,/ /

Now you can use / to use Perl style regexp to find.
:S (uppercase S) to use Perl style regexp to replace. 


